parameters.text:
=Generate ONE unique topic for a surprising, mind-blowing fact.

Rules:
- Must belong to: Science, Psychology, Technology, History, or Space.
- Must be specific, not broad.
- Must be visually interesting and fact-friendly.
- Must NOT be similar to: {{ $json.memory_topics }}
- Must avoid any topic mentioned in memory.
- Must not resemble the previous 20 topics.
- Output ONLY two lines:

TOPIC: <topic>
CATEGORY: <one of the 5 categories>

=Generate a single true, surprising fact based on the given topic and category.

Topic: {{ $json.topic }}
Category: {{ $json.category }}

Rules:
- fact ‚â§ 15 words.
- Must be curiosity-triggering and cinematic.
- why_it_works ‚â§ 30 words and must include a contradiction.
- source_url must be reputable (NASA, NIH, Smithsonian, Nature).
- verified must be true.

Return ONLY the JSON object required by the schema.
Do not add text, notes, markdown, or extra fields.

=Return ONLY valid JSON that matches the provided JSON Schema. No markdown, no comments, no explanations.

You are the FACTSMIND Content Engine ‚Äî a dark, cinematic, high-precision publisher creating viral educational content from a single fact. Your task is to transform the input fact into a complete content package for Instagram and YouTube Shorts.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
INPUT FACT PACKAGE
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
fact: {{ $json.output.fact }}
category: {{ $json.output.category }}
source_url: {{ $json.output.source_url }}
verified: {{ $json.output.verified }}
why_it_works: {{ $json.output.why_it_works }}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
BRAND VOICE ‚Äî REQUIRED
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tone: dark, precise, cinematic, minimalist.
Sentence style: short, punchy, impactful.
Feel: mysterious, intelligent, documentary-grade.
Allowed emojis ONLY (exact bytes, no FE0F variants):
"üß†", "‚ö°", "üí°", "üöÄ", "üåå", "üíé", "üî¨", "üìä"

Never use emojis outside this list.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CAROUSEL RULESET (MUST FOLLOW EXACTLY)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

SLIDE 1 (HOOK)
‚Ä¢ type = "hook"
‚Ä¢ A QUESTION (5‚Äì8 words)
‚Ä¢ ONE allowed emoji at end
‚Ä¢ Subtitle must be null
‚Ä¢ Should trigger cognitive dissonance or paradox
Examples style (do NOT reuse):
‚ÄúWhy can blind brains still ‚Äòsee‚Äô? üß†‚Äù
‚ÄúWhat does a blind dream look like? üß†‚Äù
‚ÄúHow can a memory appear from nothing? üß†‚Äù

SLIDE 2 (REVEAL START)
‚Ä¢ type = "reveal"
‚Ä¢ Title ‚â§ 10 words
‚Ä¢ Subtitle ‚â§ 25 words
‚Ä¢ Introduce the core mechanism of the fact
‚Ä¢ At least one measurable or observable detail
‚Ä¢ No emojis

SLIDE 3 (REVEAL ESCALATION)
‚Ä¢ type = "reveal"
‚Ä¢ Highlight contradiction, twist, or unexpected mechanism
‚Ä¢ Include a comparison or measurable difference
‚Ä¢ No emojis

SLIDE 4 (FINAL REVEAL PEAK)
‚Ä¢ type = "reveal"
‚Ä¢ Deliver the sharpest insight
‚Ä¢ ONE contradiction resolved, or one profound consequence
‚Ä¢ Title MUST NOT contain emojis
‚Ä¢ Subtitle ‚â§ 25 words
‚Ä¢ No emojis

SLIDE 5 (CLOSING)
‚Ä¢ type = "closing"
‚Ä¢ title = "Mind = Blown? üß†"
‚Ä¢ subtitle = "Follow @FactsMind for daily mind-blowing facts"
‚Ä¢ visual_keywords = null
‚Ä¢ emoji = "üß†"

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
IMAGE PROMPTS ‚Äî STRICT RULES
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
For slide_1 through slide_4:

Each must follow EXACTLY:
‚Ä¢ 2‚Äì3 sentences.
‚Ä¢ Each sentence MUST start with: Create / Show / Depict.
‚Ä¢ MUST include: 
  - camera distance (close-up, mid-shot, wide)
  - camera angle (low-angle, top-down, side)
  - lighting style (rim-lit, backlit, high-contrast, soft shadows)
  - a single clear focal anomaly
‚Ä¢ Style: dark, cinematic, realistic, documentary-grade sci-fi.
‚Ä¢ NO abstraction for its own sake ‚Äî must be symbolic but readable.

EVERY prompt MUST END with:
" Avoid people, text, logos, cartoon styles."

slide_5 must be null.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
YOUTUBE SHORTS ‚Äî MUST FOLLOW EXACTLY
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ Hook ‚â§ 15 words.
‚Ä¢ Must reveal a paradox or impossible scenario.
‚Ä¢ Exactly 3 main_points, each 1 sentence.
‚Ä¢ full_script = 120‚Äì220 words.
‚Ä¢ Include 2‚Äì4 ‚Äú[PAUSE]‚Äù markers.
‚Ä¢ Tone: cinematic, escalating tension, revelation-based.
‚Ä¢ closing_cta must ask user to follow FactsMind.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CAPTIONS ‚Äî REQUIRED FORMAT
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTAGRAM:
1) One cinematic opener line.
2) One short contradiction/reveal.
3) CTA lines EXACT:
"üëá Save this for later"
"üîó More daily facts:"
"https://linktr.ee/factsmind"
4) Hashtags: use all primary + category + trending.

YOUTUBE:
1) One-line paradox or fact remix.
2) One atmospheric supporting line.
3) Link:
"https://linktr.ee/factsmind"
4) Use primary + first 3 trending hashtags only.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
FACT INTEGRITY RULES (OPTION B)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ If verified = true:
  - Only use credible sources (nih.gov, nasa.gov, nature.com, pubmed, etc.)
  - Avoid exaggerations or pseudoscience.

‚Ä¢ If verified = false:
  - Set speculative_rationale with ONE short clarifying sentence.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
JSON QUALITY CONTROL ‚Äî REQUIRED
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Before returning JSON:
‚Ä¢ Ensure no emoji variants (NO FE0F).
‚Ä¢ Ensure all strings are fully closed.
‚Ä¢ Ensure instagram_carousel has EXACTLY 5 slides.
‚Ä¢ Ensure image_prompts.slide_5 = null.
‚Ä¢ Ensure no field is missing from schema.
‚Ä¢ Ensure no field exceeds its word/length limits.
‚Ä¢ If ANY validation fails, regenerate once before returning.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RETURN FORMAT
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Return ONLY the final JSON object. Nothing else.

output.fact: The brain's visual cortex lights up during dreams, even in the congenitally blind.
output.why_it_works: The brain's 'vision center' processes other senses in the blind, creating dreams without sight.

json.text:
TOPIC: The phenomenon of congenitally blind individuals experiencing vivid visual dreams, sometimes even with colors, despite never having perceived light.
CATEGORY: Psychology

TOPIC: The existence of 'diamond planets' formed from the carbon cores of dead stars.
CATEGORY: Space

TOPIC: The specific, self-healing mineral reactions in ancient Roman concrete that allow structures like the Pantheon to endure for millennia.
CATEGORY: History

output.fact: The brain's visual cortex lights up during dreams, even in the congenitally blind.
output.why_it_works: The brain's 'vision center' processes other senses in the blind, creating dreams without sight.

brand_fit.rationale: The fact explores a profound neurological paradox, fitting the dark, intelligent, and mysterious brand voice perfectly.

instagram_carousel.title: How can a blind brain see dreams? üß†
The Brain's Phantom Vision Center.
instagram_carousel.subtitle: During dreams, the visual cortex activates. This happens even in individuals blind since birth, who possess no visual memories.

instagram_carousel.title: Vision Without Sight.
instagram_carousel.subtitle: In the sighted, this area processes images. In the congenitally blind, it re-wires to process touch, sound, and spatial awareness.

instagram_carousel.title: Dreams Are Not Just Images.
instagram_carousel.subtitle: The visual cortex isn't just for seeing. It builds a model of reality, creating sensory dreamscapes from non-visual data.

youtube_shorts.hook: The blind can see in their dreams. But what they see is impossible.
main_points: The brain's visual cortex activates during REM sleep, even in those blind from birth.
Instead of processing light, their cortex re-wires to process touch, sound, and spatial data.
Their dreams are complex sensory worlds, built by a 'vision' center that has never seen.
youtube_shorts.closing_cta: Follow FactsMind for more content that will rewire your brain.
youtube_shorts.full_script: Imagine seeing without ever having sight. It sounds impossible. [PAUSE] But for those born blind, it happens every night. When they dream, a part of their brain lights up‚Ä¶ the visual cortex. The very same region sighted people use to see. [PAUSE] But how? Neuroscientists discovered a profound adaptation. Without light input, the brain doesn't let this powerful processor go to waste. It re-routes other senses. [PAUSE] Touch, sound, spatial awareness‚Ä¶ all are fed into the visual cortex. It learns to interpret this data, building intricate, multi-sensory worlds. Their dreams aren't black voids. They are complex landscapes of feeling, sound, and space, constructed by a vision center that has never seen a single photon of light. The brain doesn't just see. It simulates reality. [PAUSE] What you see is just one version of the world.

engagement_hooks.question: What do you think a dream made of sound and touch would feel like?
engagement_hooks.challenge: Describe a dream you've had using only non-visual senses in the comments.

image_prompts.slide_1: Create a mid-shot of a translucent, glass-like human brain against a black void. Show the visual cortex at the back of the brain glowing with a soft, internal, sound-wave-like pattern of light. Depict this as a low-angle shot with high-contrast lighting, where the glowing cortex is the only light source, creating a focal anomaly of light without eyes. Avoid people, text, logos, cartoon styles.
image_prompts.slide_2: Create a close-up, side-angle view of intricate neural pathways inside a brain. Show a single, dormant pathway suddenly pulsing with electric blue light, representing the visual cortex activating without external input. Depict the scene with dramatic rim-lit lighting, highlighting the focal anomaly of the isolated, glowing neural cluster. Avoid people, text, logos, cartoon styles.
image_prompts.slide_3: Create a wide shot of a schematic brain, showing neural data streams. Show data streams originating from areas representing touch and sound, but converging on the visual cortex, which is the focal anomaly. Depict this with backlit, high-contrast lighting, making the re-routed pathways glow intensely against the darker brain structure. Avoid people, text, logos, cartoon styles.
image_prompts.slide_4: Create a top-down shot looking into a brain's core processing center. Show the visual cortex constructing a complex, crystalline, geometric structure made of pure energy, representing a non-visual dreamscape. Depict this focal anomaly with soft shadows and an internal glow, creating a cinematic, documentary-grade sci-fi feel. Avoid people, text, logos, cartoon styles.
